    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Liturgical objects in the form of small lances or spears, used in the Greek Church used in the preparatory rite of prothesis, during which the host is separated from a loaf before consecration.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
